message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories as it proposes a neural network-based approach for multi-organ segmentation. The use of anatomical priors also suggests that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. Additionally, the focus on medical imaging and the use of empirical distributions may place it in the medical imaging (cs.MED) category. Finally, the use of stochastic primal-dual gradient algorithm may suggest that it belongs to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NEURON) category.
